text: This is already posted in the general channel, but figured I’d post here too. CMS custom objects aren’t being recognized in the react (or HubL) modules as of this morning:
I have already seen another post about it from a different user, so it isn’t just us.

Hi <@U02G7H60YCS>. I get the following build error in my project:
```Error building JS Project with error message `x Build failed in 276ms` and cause `Build failure`. Check your react build logs for more information```
But how can I check my React build logs? I can't fix the error without more information. Can you help me here?
Many thanks in advance!

Hey Arno — in your portal if you click on CRM development in the sidebar -> Projects -> Your project card

You then should be able to see any failed builds. Clicking on the failed build will show you the logs.
Thx for the quick reply. But all I can see there is the error message I mentioned above already.
Hmmm that is not helpful — Can you DM me your portal ID?
(also did you try to upload again?)
Yes, I even deleted the whole project and uploaded it again. That helped in the passed with other issues, but cannot be a solution for live projects.

> Yes, I even deleted the whole project and uploaded it again. That helped in the passed with other issues, but cannot be a solution for live projects.
Correct — I wouldn’t recommend deleting your projects. I think react project pipeline is also in a better beta state than it used to be. I don’t think deleting the projects will be the fix any longer. Although the good news is that if you delete a project and then upload it again with the same name it will still hook up to everything that it originally was (I think)
Great! Looks like that error matches what I was seeing (assuming that was from the local preview)
Yes it does. But how did you get your log? That would help me next time to debug my project?

That log — unfortunately — is happening elsewhere in the build pipeline and you won’t be able to access it. Will pass that along to the JSR team to see if there is a way it can be surfaced in the logs UI.
That would be definitely great! Currently developers have a blind spot when it comes to build debugging.
I would say that in my experience with HS react building the majority of the logs do come through to where I mentioned above. However, it seems like a few are still slipping through the cracks.

However, in the interim, usually checking those logs + localhost preview the various modules will likely surface the issue. Not an ideal workflow to need to preview the modules but as a last ditch effort in the interim def worth a shot if youre stuck!

Thank you BJ, you made my day. The react dev experience is already quite good compared to the HubL way to do things. Have been working with HubL for about 8 years now and I really appreciate the new degrees of freedom developing with React in HubSpot.
Love to hear it! Have a good weekend!
You too. See you soon here in the channel.
